summary:
The Security Council, recalling its previous resolutions on Somalia, determines that Al-Shabaab's attempts to undermine peace and security constitute a threat to international peace and security. Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter, it:

1. Renews provisions on measures against Al-Shabaab, including on IED components, until 28 February 2025;
2. Extends the mandate of the Panel of Experts until 31 March 2025 and intends to review the mandate by 28 February 2025;
3. Remains actively seized of the matter.
